      {
        "id": "comment_intro",
        "parent_id": null,
        "type": "nodetool.workflows.base_node.Comment",
        "data": {
          "comment": "# 📚 Chat With Your Documents (RAG)\n\nAsk questions against your own documents instead of the model's memory. Each document is indexed into a **vector collection**, a search keyword pulls the matching passages back out, and an LLM writes the answer **only** from what was retrieved — citing the source of every claim.\n\n**Pipeline:** Documents → index into collection · Search keyword → retrieve passages → build grounded prompt → cited answer\n\n**Why a graph:** the retrieval step is separate from the generation step, so you can swap the corpus, inspect exactly which passages were used, and keep the model from inventing facts. A chat box can't show you that.\n\n**Try this:** edit the documents, or change the search keyword to `warranty` to scope retrieval to one topic.\n\n**Retrieval:** the search keyword is matched against the indexed passages — `Aurora` appears in every document, so the whole corpus comes back and the model can answer any question about it. Narrow the keyword to retrieve a subset. The collection is set up with the Ollama `nomic-embed-text` embedding model for semantic vector search.",
          "headline": "Chat With Your Documents"
        },
        "ui_properties": {
          "selected": false,
          "position": {
            "x": -620,
            "y": 40
          },
          "zIndex": 0,
          "width": 520,
          "height": 300,
          "selectable": true
        },
